      • mode

        public static <T> java.util.List<T> mode(java.util.List<T> xs)
        Given an array of ints, find the maximum number of occurrences of any value, and return an array of all items that occurred that max number of times. Developer's Note: this uses the contains method.
        Parameters:
        xs - array of int values
        Returns:
        array of mode values (all occur the most in the array)

      • uniques

        public static <T> java.util.List<T> uniques(java.util.List<T> values)
        Given a List of values, creates a new List that only includes each unique value exactly once, in order of their first occurrence from lowest to highest index. When actual parameter values is null, returns an empty List. Note that null is treated as just another value; when present in List values, it should also be included in the returned List. When values is empty, the answer is also empty. Developer's Note: this is used by mode, and this uses contains.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of elemetns in values list
        Parameters:
        values - List of values to inspect, collecting
        Returns:
        List of the unique values

      • contains

        public static <T> boolean contains(java.util.List<T> xs,
                                   T value)
        Given a List and a value to seek, scans through the list and if it finds a match, it returns true; if no match is found, it returns false. If the List xs is null, nothing can be found. Actual parameter value may be null, and the return value will indicate if null is stored in xs. Developer's Note: this is used by uniques.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of elements in list xs
        Parameters:
        xs - List of values to search through
        value - value to seek
        Returns:
        whether value was found in xs or not
